Eskom has on Saturday announced that it has terminated the services of its evidence leader, Sebetja Matsaung, in the disciplinary hearing of suspended Eskom executive Matshela Koko. This follows an altercation between Matsaung and Financial Mail’s Deputy Editor Sikonathi Mantshantsha after the hearing was adjourned yesterday. Related:http://www.thenewage.co.za/matshela-koko-to-face-disciplinary-hearing/ “Eskom condemns Matsaung’s behaviour in the strongest terms possible. We wish to convey our unreserved apologies that this unfortunate incident occurred. “The hearing, which is due to recommence on Monday, will be postponed until a new evidence leader is appointed. We anticipate that this will take up to three days to finalise,” Eskom said in a statement. Watch:http://www.thenewage.co.za/matshela-koko-faces-disciplinary-hearing/ Eskom added that they will update on developments on all communication platforms. TNA Reporter    